<title>UK: LucasVarity buys back shares at 185p/share.</title>
<headline>LucasVarity buys back shares at 185p/share.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-04-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>British auto and aerospace engineering group LucasVarity Plc said on Monday it bought back 2.5 million of its shares at a price of about 185p per share.</p>
<p>The firm said it bought the shares, which represented some 0.2 percent of its ordinary shares, from Hoare Govett Securities Ltd.</p>
<p>LucasVarity's shares closed down 5.5p at 184. Earlier this month, the firm launched a programme to buy back 80 million stg of shares as part of its efforts to satisfy investors on both sides of the Atlantic.</p>
<p>The company was formed from the merger last year of Britain's Lucas and U.S. group Varity Corp.  </p>
